            "votes_up": 2,
            "weighted_score": 0.5454545617103577,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Farming Simulator 19 is one of those games that slowly becomes a huge part of your gaming life without you really noticing it. You start out with a small farm and basic equipment, just trying things out, and before long you’re managing huge fields, expensive machines and a full farming operation.\nWith over 1712.9 hours played, it clearly shows how deep and addictive the game is.\nWhat makes it so enjoyable is the freedom and progression. You decide everything yourself, from what crops to grow, which machines to buy, and how to expand your farm. Every successful harvest feels rewarding because you actually built it up from nothing.\nThe gameplay loop is calm but very satisfying. Driving tractors, planting, harvesting and managing your land creates a relaxing rhythm that you can get lost in for hours. It’s not a stressful game, but it still always gives you something to improve or work toward.\nThe attention to detail in machinery and farming systems makes it feel realistic and immersive. You don’t just play a farmer, you actually feel like you are running a real farm.\n\nRating 10 out of 10\nA relaxing, deep and highly addictive simulation that turns farming into something you never get tired of."
        },
